            </ul>
        """
    },
    Acrophobia: {
        type: ["Mental"],
        flavor: """
            <p><em>The sniper position was perfect. Sixth floor, corner office, clear sightlines across the entire intersection. The spotter set up without hesitation. His partner stopped at the window.</em></p>
            <p>"You need to be prone at the glass."</p>
            <p>"I know where I need to be."</p>
            <p>"Then get there."</p>
            <p><em>He knelt. Crawled forward. Got within two meters of the window and stopped. Through the broken glass, the street was six stories straight down. His stomach dropped like he'd missed a step on a staircase.</em></p>
            <p>"I can shoot from here."</p>
            <p>"You can't see the south approach from there."</p>
            <p>"Then you cover the south approach."</p>
            <p><em>The spotter looked at him. Looked at the window. Looked back.</em></p>
            <p>"Alright. I've got south. You stay there."</p>
