        """,
        description: """
            <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Height isn't the problem. The problem is that some part of your brain is absolutely certain you're going to fall, and no amount of railing, harness, or solid floor changes its mind. Balconies, catwalks, rappelling, helicopter doors: your body locks up and your vision narrows to the drop.</li>
                <li>You gain 3 strife whenever you are at significant height with visible exposure (upper floors near windows, rooftops, catwalks, ladders, rappelling, open helicopter doors).</li>
                <li>The first time this anxiety applies in a scene, you gain 1 fortune point.</li>
            </ul>
        """
    },
    Nyctophobia: {
        type: ["Mental"],
        flavor: """
            <p><em>Power went out at 0200. Standard Green Zone brownout, nothing unusual. The backup generator would kick in within ninety seconds. Most of the squad rolled over and went back to sleep. One reached for her weapon light and turned it on immediately.</em></p>
            <p>"Go back to sleep, Park."</p>
            <p>"I'm fine. Just checking."</p>
            <p>"Checking what? The dark?"</p>
            <p><em>Silence. The weapon light swept the room once, twice. Corners, doorway, window. The generator hummed to life and the overheads flickered back on. Park turned off the light but didn't put it down.</em></p>
