        description: """
            <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Contamination is everywhere, and you are the only person who takes it seriously. Surfaces, shared equipment, other people's hands: the world is a petri dish and everyone in it is a vector. This has nothing to do with Collapse Radiation. This is older, more fundamental. Dirt. Disease. The invisible things that accumulate when people stop paying attention.</li>
                <li>You gain 3 strife whenever you must use unsanitary facilities, share personal equipment, touch surfaces of unknown cleanliness, or be in close physical proximity with someone whose hygiene you find questionable.</li>
                <li>The first time this anxiety applies in a scene, you gain 1 fortune point.</li>
            </ul>
        """
    },
    Martyr: {
        type: ["Mental"],
        flavor: """
            <p><em>The supply drop was short. Not enough rations for the full squad for three days. The math was simple: someone had to eat less. The operator volunteered before anyone finished counting.</em></p>
            <p>"I'll cut my intake. I can run on half rations."</p>
            <p>"Nobody needs to run on half rations. We'll redistribute."</p>
            <p>"Redistribute means everyone eats less. One person eating less means everyone else eats enough. The math is obvious."</p>
            <p>"You did this last time."</p>
            <p>"And it worked last time."</p>
            <p><em>The squad leader studied her. This wasn't the first sacrifice. It was the pattern: first watch, last meal, worst sleeping position, heaviest load. Every burden that could be absorbed, she absorbed. It looked like selflessness. After the fifth time, it started looking like something else.</em></p>
            <p>"You don't have to be the one who suffers every time."</p>
            <p>"Someone has to."</p>
