        description: """
            <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>If someone has to suffer, it should be you. You volunteer for the worst duty, absorb every hardship, and refuse help with a consistency that has stopped looking like generosity and started looking like self-punishment. You need to be the one who gives, and you cannot articulate why taking feels so much worse.</li>
                <li>You gain 3 strife whenever someone else suffers a hardship you could have taken in their place, whenever you are forced to accept help or comfort, or whenever you are prevented from sacrificing for the group.</li>
