            </ul>
        """
    },
    "Control Freak": {
        type: ["Mental"],
        flavor: """
            <p><em>The joint operation had a simple command structure: their squad handles north, the militia handles south. Two independent elements, one objective. The operator couldn't leave it alone.</em></p>
            <p>"What's the militia's breach sequence?"</p>
            <p>"That's their problem."</p>
            <p>"Their problem becomes our problem if they breach early and push hostiles into our sector."</p>
            <p>"They've done this before."</p>
            <p>"Have they done it well?"</p>
            <p><em>She spent the next hour reviewing the militia's plan, annotating it, sending corrections through the liaison, and requesting a joint rehearsal that nobody had asked for. The militia commander sent back a polite refusal. She sent back a revised plan annotated with everything that could go wrong if they didn't rehearse.</em></p>
